
Project Brief: Hospi - Hospital Management System

Hospi is a comprehensive hospital management web application built with the MERN stack that facilitates appointment booking between patients and doctors with admin oversight.
Core Functionality: 
Patients/Users: Register, book appointments, manage profiles, make payments
Doctors: Manage availability, view appointments, update profiles, track earnings
Admin: Manage doctors, view all appointments, monitor system dashboard


Technology Stack Used:

ðŸš€ Frontend Technologies 
Core Framework
React.js - JavaScript library for building user interfaces
React DOM - DOM renderer for React    
Routing 
React Router DOM - Client-side routing for React applications
State Management  
React Context API - For global state management
React Hooks (useState, useEffect, useContext) - For state and lifecycle management
HTTP Client 
Axios - Promise-based HTTP client for API calls 
Styling & UI
Tailwind CSS - Utility-first CSS framework
Notifications
React Toastify - Toast notifications library
Development Tools
Vite - Fast build tool and development server (based on your error messages)






Backend:
Node.js - Runtime environment
Express.js - Web framework
MongoDB - Database
Mongoose - MongoDB ODM
JWT - Authentication (jsonwebtoken)
bcryptjs - Password hashing  
validator - Input validation 
multer - File upload handling
cloudinary - Image storage
cors - Cross-origin resource sharing
dotenv - Environment variables


Development Tools:
nodemon - Development server auto-restart
Git - Version control
VS Code - Code editor

Architecture:
RESTful API - Backend API design
MVC Pattern - Models, Views, Controllers 
Middleware - Authentication & file upload
Environment Configuration - .env for secrets

Key Features Implemented:
User Authentication (JWT tokens)
Role-based Access (Admin, Doctor, User)
Appointment Management (Booking, Cancellation, Completion)
Image Upload (Cloudinary for doctor/user profiles)
Database Operations (CRUD operations with MongoDB)
Input Validation & Error handling
File Upload with multer middleware

Security Measures:
Password hashing with bcrypt
JWT token-based authentication
Input validation and sanitization
Environment variables for sensitive data


